<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_Sim_Skewer_Sim_Control" s="74221">
  <T n="category">10175<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_category_SimLife--></T>
  <T n="name">0xD1C36CD8<!--String: "Controlling Sims"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\LiveMode\LiveMode_ControllingSims_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:4594886863c372cc</T>
      <T n="text">0xAC05CCCA<!--String: "Sims will do things <b><font color='#199C2C'>on their own</font></b>, but why let them have all the fun? Shape your Sims’ lives by giving them some much needed <b><font color='#199C2C'>guidance</font></b>!\n\nAt the bottom of the screen, you can find a row of <b><font color='#199C2C'>thumbnails</font></b>, representing each Sim in your current household. This is where you select which Sim to <b><font color='#199C2C'>control</font></b>. \n\nYou can also use the [Spacebar] to change your active Sim.\n\nYour active Sim has a green, yellow, orange, or red crystal hovering above their head. That's the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Plumbob</font></b>! Its color indicates the state of the Sim's Needs."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\LiveMode\LiveMode_ControllingSims_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:4594886863c372cf</T>
      <T n="text">0x65118974<!--String: "<b><font color='#199C2C'>Click</font></b> on the ground, an Object, or a Sim to reveal the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Interaction menu</font></b>! \n\nHere you will find all the Interactions your controlled Sim has available with the thing you clicked on. More interactions can be <b><font color='#199C2C'>unlocked</font></b> with higher Relationship scores, Skill levels etc."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\LiveMode\LiveMode_ControllingSims_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:4594886863c372ce</T>
      <T n="text">0x3341DC9<!--String: "When you select something in an Interaction menu, it will appear in the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Action Queue</font></b>.\n\nIf you’re in a hurry (or changed your mind), you can click on any actions in the queue to <b><font color='#199C2C'>cancel</font></b> them."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\LiveMode\LiveMode_ControllingSims_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:4594886863c372c9</T>
      <T n="text">0xF4E22E99<!--String: "<b><font color='#199C2C'>Right-click</font></b> on a Sim’s thumbnail to <b><font color='#199C2C'>center the Game Camera</font></b> on them.\n\nThe <b><font color='#199C2C'>Home icon</font></b> will appear when your Sim is away from their home lot. Clicking this will send them home.\n\nAn <b><font color='#199C2C'>Away Action icon</font></b> appears on Sims who are not in the currently loaded Neighborhood. Clicking it will display different options for you to direct your Sim from afar. You can also choose to bring that Sim to you, or send yourself to that Sim through this menu."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
